HEADWORD: Dives
<hw>Di"ves</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., rich.]</ety>
<def>The name popularly given to the rich man in our Lord's parable of
the ⟦ldquo⟧Rich Man and Lazarus⟦rdquo⟧ (<au>Luke xvi. 19-31</au>).
Hence, a name for a rich worldling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Divest</ent>⟦br⟧
